-- U.S. Stock Futures Fluctuate a Day After Market Ceases Slide
-- Michael P. Regan
-- 2010-07-07T12:46:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-07/u-s-stock-futures-fluctuate-after-dow-average-snaps-seven-days-of-losses.html

          
          
             U.S. stock-index futures fluctuated a
day after the Dow Jones Industrial Average snapped a seven-day
losing streak, its longest slump since the financial crisis of
2008.  
 Futures on the Standard & Poorâ€™s 500 Index were unchanged
at 1,024.2 at 8:44 a.m. in New York after slumping as much as
0.8 percent earlier. Dow Jones Industrial Average futures
slipped 3 points, or less than 0.1 percent, to 9,679.  
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                            
                     
